author: dlydick
msg: Changed CASE_SENSE_NAMES and SHORT_NAMES both to YES for better
support of Windows and CygWin distros.  The 'winzip' utility cannot
handle really long file names coming out of .tar.gz files and it
puts them in the top level directory of the output area, occasionally
suffixing them with digits in their names.
Change MAX_INITIALIZER_LINES from default to 50 lines, which should
cover even the length of the longest macros.
